FBIS3-37059 "drsov030_b_94030" FBIS-SOV-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic & Space Issues Chernomyrdin: 1994 Budget May Have `Big Deficit' LD1002180194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1727 GMT 10 FeB 94 LD1002180194 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Ivanov] [Text] Moscow February 10 TASS -- The draft budget for 1994 will be finalised in the near future, Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin said on Thursday at a meeting with representatives of the parliamentary bloc New Regional Policy, which has the second largest faction in the State Duma. The faction members who represent the interests of Russian regions brought up the problem of non-payments, state support for the Far North, inflation and the problem of refugees at the meeting. Chernomyrdin said that the draft budget for 1994 may envisage a "big deficit." He urged the enterprises to provide their guarantees that they will continue making vital products in the required volume. He stressed the need to foster closer "working" ties between the government and the Federal Assembly.
